249
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,006
‐ Wait a second, you
two look familiar.

250
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:00,012
Have I met you somewhere before?

251
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:01,974
‐ [Both] No, I don’t
believe you have, mam.

252
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:03,725
‐ Really, are you sure?

253
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,058
‐ Yes, mam.

254
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:12,229
‐ [Loud Speaker] Miss Kazami,
you have a telephone call.

255
00:12:12,315 --> 00:12:15,785
Please, come to the teacher’s
office as soon as possible.

256
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:17,032
‐ I’m sorry, would you mind

257
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,201
if I stepped out
for a few minutes?

258
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,409
I won’t be long.

259
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:21,279
‐ [Both] Yes, please, go away.

260
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:22,577
‐ What did you say?

261
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,410
‐ [Both] Oh, nothing.

262
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:26,155
(gasp)

263
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:28,406
Oribe and Kamishiro.

264
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,879
‐ Mam.
‐ Hello, Miss Kazami.

265
00:12:30,959 --> 00:12:32,079
‐ It’s Mr. Mike.

266
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,300
‐ And I’ve heard that
voice somewhere before.

267
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:39,262
It’s that Simpi that came
to our house the other day.

268
00:12:39,384 --> 00:12:40,514
‐ [Karen] I don’t get it.

269
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,933
What is Mike doing
all alone with her?

270
00:12:42,053 --> 00:12:43,683
What’s the meaning of all this?

271
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:46,773
‐ Listen, Kamishiro, regarding
that thing we talked about?

272
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:48,521
‐ [Mike] Yeah, I was gonna
have a chat about that

273
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,981
a few minutes ago, but
I got a great answer.

274
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:52,774
I’m planning on visiting
the parents later

275
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:53,975
and giving them my greetings.

276
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:55,437
‐ What does he mean, greetings?

277
00:12:55,525 --> 00:12:56,825
‐ What does he mean, parents?

278
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,613
‐ So they’re that important?

279
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:01,156
Kamishiro, you just met
them a few days ago,

280
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:03,321
these people may
be total strangers.

281
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:05,989
‐ That’s true but they
could be my real relatives.

282
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:07,039
‐ [Miina] Can you hear them?

283
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,620
‐ [Karen] Yeah, barely.

284
00:13:08,705 --> 00:13:10,875
‐ Look, you really don’t know
enough to be certain, do you?

285
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:12,577
How about you have
them take a blood test

286
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:13,917
and then you can
find out for sure

287
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:16,002
if they’re really
relatives or not.

288
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:18,959
‐ Simpi, I’ve already done
some research about that.

289
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:21,590
The only way to know
for sure is DNA analysis

290
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:23,796
and that cost 100,000 yen.

291
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:26,848
I don’t have that kind of
money laying around anywhere.

292
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:27,813
Besides.

293
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:30,522
‐ Yeah, besides what, Kamishiro?

294
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,313
(angelic music)

295
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:38,322
‐ It’s like this, I
have something right now

296
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:39,993
that I’ve wanted my whole life

297
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,118
and it amazingly appeared
right in front of my face.

298
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:47,332
‐ Oh, Kamishiro, I‐‐

299
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:49,122
‐ Stop, right there!

300
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:52,541
All interior relationships
are forbidden!

301
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:53,825
‐ Miss Miina, no!

302
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,206
‐ [Miina] And when I
say it’s forbidden,

303
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:56,505
I mean it’s forbidden!

304
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:58,087
‐ Who was that?

305
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,591
‐ [Miina] I’m a teacher!

306
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,262
‐ I don’t know any teach
here who sounds like that.

307
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:03,842
‐ Hey, this is kinda suspicious.

308
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:05,848
‐ It was coming from
that room, wasn’t it?

309
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:07,178
‐ [Mike] Should
we open the door?

310
00:14:07,305 --> 00:14:08,935
‐ Of course, we need
to inform the teachers

311
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,935
if there’s someone
suspicious in there.

312
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:11,847
‐ [Miina] This isn’t good.

313
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:14,806
‐ Well, no, of course it isn’t.

314
00:14:14,896 --> 00:14:15,766
‐ Who is it?

315
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,685
(whimsical music)

316
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,530
Simpi, there they are!

317
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:29,789
‐ [Simpi] Escaping
from the window

318
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,499
makes them all the
more suspicious.

319
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:33,209
‐ Miss Miina,
didn’t we come here

320
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:35,539
so that we could interview
for a job opening?

321
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,795
‐ You don’t mind my
framing you here?

322
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,547
‐ No, that’s unacceptable.

323
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:41,590
‐ Then you better keep running.

324
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:43,424
(whimpering)

325
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:46,339
‐ [Karen] Miss
Miina, what’s wrong?

326
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:48,887
‐ I think I twisted my foot.

327
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:50,561
Don’t worry, I’m all right.

328
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:51,851
‐ All right, I’m back.

329
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:54,063
I’m sorry to have kept
you waiting so long.

330
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:57,815
(sighing)

331
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,703
‐ [Both] One, two, three, four.

332
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:07,620
Two, two, three, four.

333
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:08,530
Three, two, three, four.

334
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,196
‐ They’re not in there.

335
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,744
‐ They’re not over here either.

336
00:15:11,828 --> 00:15:13,748
I better go inform the
student body president

337
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:14,581
about all this.

338
00:15:14,664 --> 00:15:15,504
‐ I’ll go with you.

339
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:18,254
‐ Looks like we were
able to fool ’em.

340
00:15:18,376 --> 00:15:20,706
‐ I can’t believe we
stole these gym clothes.

341
00:15:20,795 --> 00:15:24,425
(sobbing) I’m turning more
and more into a bad girl.

342
00:15:26,092 --> 00:15:29,682
‐ Someone stole all my gym
clothes out of my locker.

343
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,602
‐ Someone took mine too.

344
00:15:31,681 --> 00:15:34,431
‐ Mine are all right, see?

345
00:15:34,517 --> 00:15:35,937
‐ What happened, Haruko?

346
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,440
(girls gasp)

347
00:15:39,397 --> 00:15:41,727
(screaming)

348
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:45,437
It’s a misunderstanding,
I was just!

349
00:15:45,528 --> 00:15:46,778
‐ [Female Student]
Two suspicious people

350
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,324
are running around campus?

351
00:15:48,448 --> 00:15:51,778
A couple of freshman girls
had their gym clothes stolen?

352
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:54,239
‐ [Male Student] I heard
one guy got caught.

353
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:55,448
‐ [Female Student] And
I heard the other one

354
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:56,830
is still on the loose.

355
00:15:56,956 --> 00:16:00,286
‐ [Girls] Oh no!

356
00:16:00,418 --> 00:16:02,288
‐ Call out the Manners
Committee Members,

357
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,918
you’re to work together
with the teachers

358
00:16:04,005 --> 00:16:06,305
to blockade every entrance
and exit to this school.

359
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:09,512
‐ You really think we need to
go that far, Madam President?

360
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:12,295
‐ I do, we need to be
thorough about this.

361
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,805
(dramatic music)

362
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,405
‐ [Female Student] Should we
check this room just in case?

363
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:32,831
‐ [Male Student] Yeah, I got it.

364
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:33,740
‐ What do you see, Miss Miina?

365
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,116
What’s going on now?

366
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:35,953
‐ [Miina] It looks
like they’re doing

367
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:37,197
a search at the school.

368
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:39,160
‐ Oh no, this isn’t happening.

369
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:44,248
We’re really gonna
end up as criMiinals.

370
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:49,378
‐ Na!
(gasp)

371
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:50,339
Mr. Marie.

372
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:53,761
‐ Now, how did this
one get in here?

373
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,346
‐ Na, na, na, na‐‐

374
00:16:58,476 --> 00:16:59,726
‐ I don’t get it,
what’s it doing?

375
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:02,152
‐ It always moves
around in strange ways.

376
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:06,357
‐ So you girls were here?

377
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:09,074
(gasp)

378
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,785
‐ But how, when
did she get here?

379
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,074
‐ You mean, how
did she get here?

380
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,660
(giggling)

381
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:19,414
(bells ringing)

382
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:30,589
‐ [Student] So what did
happen to their gym clothes?

383
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,546
‐ [Simpi] Kamishiro.

384
00:17:32,677 --> 00:17:34,337
‐ Good work today, Simpi.

385
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:35,548
See you later.

386
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,770
‐ Oh, so I gather you’re
not going to help me?

387
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,140
‐ No, I have something
I need to do.

388
00:17:40,226 --> 00:17:43,096
‐ Oh, I see, are they really
that important to you?

389
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:45,309
‐ They are, now if
you’ll excuse me.

390
00:17:47,692 --> 00:17:49,032
‐ Oh, Kamishiro.

391
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,240
‐ [Kazami] Here you go.

392
00:17:53,406 --> 00:17:55,816
‐ [Karen] Thanks,
I’ll have some too.

393
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,078
‐ To think that the two of you
would go to all the trouble

394
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:00,040
of dressing up and
writing false resumes

395
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:01,711
just so you could come
to a job interview

396
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:03,459
to be office assistance.

397
00:18:04,959 --> 00:18:08,209
Do you really want to be
with Kamishiro that much?

398
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:10,416
‐ Well, uh.
‐ I guess.

399
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:13,335
‐ I see, but if he had found out

400
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:15,636
that you guys were
doing all of this,

401
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:17,931
don’t you think he
might have gotten angry?

402
00:18:21,017 --> 00:18:24,597
Of course, deep down, he
might be happy about it.

403
00:18:24,687 --> 00:18:27,437
You see, I was able to learn
quite a lot about Kamishiro

404
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:29,443
from the headmaster of
the government orphanage

405
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:31,817
that he had been in
most of his life.

406
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:34,114
Apparently, he didn’t make
any friends while he was there

407
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:36,278
and spent most of
his time all alone.

408
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,948
Although, he’d always be nice
and cordial and say hello,

409
00:18:40,036 --> 00:18:42,996
he would never play together
with any of the other orphans.

410
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:49,209
Even after he started
coming to this school,

411
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,965
he would always try to be
alone as much as possible.

412
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,592
But you see, the real
reason why Kamishiro

413
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:57,046
behaves the way he does,

414
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,046
is so that he doesn’t
have to feel responsible

415
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:01,308
for showing any
kindness to anyone.

416
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,982
He can’t possibly
abandon the people

417
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:08,272
who become deeply
involved in his life.

418
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:09,686
That may come from the fact

419
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,725
that his parents
had abandoned him.

420
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:14,989
But then you two appeared and
were suddenly in this life

421
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:16,611
that Kamishiro had built.

422
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:19,027
Suddenly, after being
alone for all this time,

423
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,198
relatives showed up.

424
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:22,909
In other words, now
that he knows you,

425
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:26,165
Kamishiro will never
be able to abandon you.

426
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:29,380
I know he may act king of
cold or aloof towards you

427
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:32,342
but I’ll bet you anything that
he’s accepted both of you.

428
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,009
That’s the way which
he shows his kindness.

429
00:19:37,301 --> 00:19:38,931
Do you understand?

430
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,851
You two are the ones
that opened the door

431
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:43,430
to the kindness that’s
been hiding inside of him.

432
00:19:45,142 --> 00:19:47,982
It looks like it’s safe
for you to go home now.

433
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:51,612
You make sure you wash and
return those gym clothes, okay?

434
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:52,571
‐ [Karen And Miina] Yes, mam.

435
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,780
(train rumbling)

436
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,663
‐ [Miina] Uh‐oh,
the door is locked.

437
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:02,030
‐ [Karen] But, Mr.
Mike’s motorbike is here.

438
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:03,329
‐ [Miina] Well,
the lights are on,

439
00:20:03,411 --> 00:20:05,751
so Mike has gotta
be inside, right?

440
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,211
‐ Hey, who’s out there?

441
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:10,627
‐ Oh, it’s me, Miina.

442
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,500
‐ And Karen, too.

443
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,877
‐ [Mike] Where
have you guys been?

444
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:17,634
Just wandering around
for all this time?

445
00:20:17,717 --> 00:20:19,087
‐ Well, I.

446
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,388
‐ [Mike] Have you guys
never thought about

447
00:20:20,511 --> 00:20:22,601
the feelings of those
who worry about you?

448
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:29,136
‐ But nobody has ever really
been worried about me before.

449
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,058
‐ [Karen] Oh, Miss Miina.

450
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,018
‐ Idiot!

451
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:35,149
Well, there’s someone
worried about you right now.

452
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:36,494
I’m worried about you.

453
00:20:36,569 --> 00:20:38,569
If I’m being pushy,
just tell me,

454
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:39,914
and I won’t care anymore.

455
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:43,580
(somber music)

456
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:46,865
‐ No, Mike, you’re
not being pushy.

457
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:50,254
‐ Yeah, I don’t think
you’re being pushy at all.

458
00:20:50,332 --> 00:20:52,292
‐ Thank you for looking
out for the two of us.

459
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:55,338
‐ I like it when people
are a little pushy.

460
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:56,551
‐ [Miina] I’m sorry, Mike.

461
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:58,420
‐ [Karen] I apologize.

462
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:01,093
‐ Then while I’m being pushy,

463
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:02,967
I guess I’ll let you know
that I managed to find

464
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,755
a couple of jobs
for both of you,

465
00:21:04,847 --> 00:21:06,517
store clerks for a nearby market

466
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:08,889
called Harry Kouwa Groceries.

467
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,766
They know about
our situation too.

468
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:14,824
‐ Oh, Mike.

469
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:15,860
‐ Mr. Mike.

470
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,986
‐ Also, I made it so that you
work in the late afternoon.

471
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:22,452
You two will be going to
school during the day.

472
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:25,446
You fine with that?

473
00:21:25,576 --> 00:21:27,906
(gasp)

474
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:30,155
Why are you dressed like that?

475
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,999
(sobbing)

476
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,955
Could it be that the strangers
who were at my school today

477
00:21:36,045 --> 00:21:36,965
were you two?

478
00:21:37,046 --> 00:21:38,456
‐ [Karen] I’m so sorry.

479
00:21:38,589 --> 00:21:40,089
‐ What were you idiots doing?

480
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:42,054
Why at school of all places?

481
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,144
‐ We went there
for job interviews

482
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,471
and while we were there, Mike,

483
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:47,314
we saw you flirting
with that Simpi.

484
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:48,969
‐ Wait a second, what
are you talking about?

485
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:51,639
‐ [Miina] You were
flirting with her!

486
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:52,807
Right?
‐ Yes.

487
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:54,897
‐ Hey, I wasn’t
doing any such thing.

488
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:56,190
‐ [Both] Yes, you were!

489
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,065
‐ [Mike] Look, don’t try
to change the subject.

490
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,650
I want you to explain to me
why you’re dressed like that.

491
00:22:00,778 --> 00:22:02,148
‐ [Karen] It’s kind
of complicated.

492
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:03,819
‐ [Miina] Hey, you’re the
one tryna change the subject!

493
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:06,238
‐ [Mike] Answer my question!

494
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:12,495
(smooth music)

495
00:23:33,621 --> 00:23:37,751
‐ [Karen And Miina] Next
episode, more twins.

496
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:38,883
‐ [Miina Voiceover] We
